<%= render 'legal_pages/legal_page_styles' %>
<div class="legal-page">
<h1>Accessibility Statement</h1>
    <p class="last-updated">Last updated: February 1, 2026</p>

    <h2>Our Commitment</h2>
    <div class="highlight">
        <p>WetWijzer/LisLoi/GesetzGuide/LexLibera is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for everyone, including people with
            disabilities. We continually improve the user experience and apply accessibility guidelines.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>Compliance Status</h2>
    <p>This website is <strong>partially</strong> compliant with the <a
            href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/standards-guidelines/wcag/">Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1</a>
        Level AA.</p>

    <h3>What We Do</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Semantic HTML:</strong> Proper use of headings, landmarks, and structure</li>
        <li><strong>Keyboard navigation:</strong> All interactive elements are keyboard accessible</li>
        <li><strong>Color contrast:</strong> Text meets minimum contrast ratios</li>
        <li><strong>Dark mode:</strong> Support for dark theme while maintaining readability</li>
        <li><strong>Responsive design:</strong> Website works on all screen sizes</li>
        <li><strong>Skip links:</strong> Ability to skip directly to main content</li>
        <li><strong>ARIA labels:</strong> Additional labels for screen readers</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Known Limitations</h3>
    <table>
        <tr>
            <th>Component</th>
            <th>Issue</th>
            <th>Alternative</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>AI Chatbot</td>
            <td>Complex interaction may be difficult for some assistive technologies</td>
            <td>Contact us via email for support</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>PDF documents</td>
            <td>Some exported documents are not fully accessible</td>
            <td>HTML version available</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>External links</td>
            <td>Links to official sources (Belgian Official Gazette) may be less accessible</td>
            <td>We have no control over external websites</td>
        </tr>
    </table>

    <h2>Technical Specifications</h2>
    <p>Accessibility of WetWijzer/LisLoi/GesetzGuide/LexLibera relies on the following technologies:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>HTML5</li>
        <li>CSS3</li>
        <li>JavaScript (with progressive enhancement)</li>
        <li>WAI-ARIA</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Feedback and Contact</h2>
    <p>We welcome feedback on the accessibility of WetWijzer/LisLoi/GesetzGuide/LexLibera. Have you experienced problems or have suggestions?
    </p>
    <div class="legal-notice">
        <p><strong>Contact:</strong></p>
        <p>Email: <a href="mailto:info@wetwijzer.be">info@wetwijzer.be</a></p>
        <p>Subject: "Accessibility"</p>
    </div>
    <p>We aim to respond within 5 business days.</p>

    <h2>Enforcement Procedure</h2>
    <p>If you have a complaint about accessibility that has not been satisfactorily resolved, you can contact:</p>
    <div class="legal-notice">
        <p><strong>Unia - Interfederal Centre for Equal Opportunities</strong></p>
        <p>Rue Royale 138, 1000 Brussels, Belgium</p>
        <p>Tel: 0800 12 800 (free within Belgium)</p>
        <p>Website: <a href="https://www.unia.be/en">www.unia.be</a></p>
    </div>
</div>
